<a href="javascript:card_browser(867)">Enduring Evil</a><br />
Teeth of mordor x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This is the deck that go with my last report, so read it for more info<br />
<br />
Fellowship:  Bid 3 and begin.  Grab Lego, play your stuff and alway stop at site 2.  If opponent bypass you, then try to slow/kill him, but follow him closely in case your shadow don&#39;t work.  If they want you to race, that great, the fellowship is pretty good and sauron cycle quite well.  Gimli is the main figter, followed by legolas.  helped by merry with escape and sword, they can kill everything.  Stealth and cliff prevent your hobbit from bitting the dust.  The big weakness is against Dunland and Tracker (if they play lurzt battle cry), but mostly dunland.  i did&#39;nt tech the deck against moria cause I don&#39;t know good moria player in my area, but in case moria is popular, just throw song of durin in the deck.  Combined with bow of the galadrim and gimli axe + choke lego= dead moria, but without song of durin, moria will probably kill you.  Stout and strong is a personal addition, but it could easily be replace.  You could also play choke frodo and no ally vs ally hater, but that just personal choice.  I like healing my merry every turn with the farmer.  Aragorn put me in range of Grima CC, but he is just too good, so I can&#39;t say no to him.  3 cliff my look too much, but drawing it first turn is nice, you end up with 0 burden, and you just discard them as soon as you need it.  Sam is there in case I don&#39;t draw cliff first turn, otherwise discard him.  Bracer could be hand axe or gimli helm, but bracer give the str +1 and can prevent wound.  Anyway, gimli don&#39;t lose skirmish very often.  Overall, the deck is good.  It is not desing to beat anything, but the survive everything.<br />
<br />
The shadow:<br />
I&#39;ve tried sauron many time before, and I&#39;ve alway end up 4-2 or 5-1, never 6-0.  But since sting and choke is gone in standart, I had guest they deserve one more chance.  It is a basic sauron direct damage deck, but without orc bowmen (cost a lot too much).  Morannon is a new great addition, giving you a good punch at site 4 and a good cycling option.  Teeth of mordor was not that useful, but it is necessery if you want to deal with large fellowship, cause late game the deck tend to lack of minions.  I make you squeak is the card that make all the difference, giving 3 pool most of the time.  Desert lord is nice with hate to kill key companion, and Desert stalker is to deal with multiple culture (better than grima in this deck, since you don&#39;t want them to heal companion but to exert).  The new tracker are just better in every point than the old one.  Basicly, with grisnak, patrol or cutthroat, all of your orc are not roaming at site 3, and they have big strenght for their cost (4 twilight for 11 strenght is good).  the small tracker are not that usefull, but they offer nice cycling option if you have too much twilight or useless card.  The patrol is the most important trakcer, cause now you get a big orc who can remove condition.  Basicly, that mean that rohan will never be able to remove your condition with fortress never fallen, and you can get rid of fearing the worst or talent for not being seen, tundering host for only 2 exertion and you still get an 11 str minion on table.  Morgul hunter and band of the eye are nice minions to wound for hate, and they win skirmish most of the time.  Band of the eye help to against deck that clog path in their hand for the final race.<br />
I think that cover it all, if you have question just ask.<br />
